    feast_date: '01-01',
    birth_year: '',
    death_year: '',
    biography: `Mary, the Mother of God, is venerated as the first and greatest of all saints. Her feast on January 1 celebrates her divine motherhood, affirmed at the Council of Ephesus in 431 AD as Theotokos — God-bearer.\n\nShe said yes to God when the angel Gabriel announced she would conceive the Son of God, and her Magnificat remains one of the most sublime prayers in Scripture. She stood at the foot of the Cross and was present in the Upper Room at Pentecost.\n\nThroughout history she has appeared to saints including Bernadette at Lourdes, Juan Diego at Guadalupe, and the children of Fatima.`,
