    id: 's-0102',
    name: 'Saints Basil and Gregory Nazianzen',
    feast_date: '01-02',
    birth_year: '329',
    death_year: '379',
    biography: `Basil the Great was Bishop of Caesarea and one of the Cappadocian Fathers who defended orthodox Trinitarian theology against Arianism. He wrote the Liturgy still used in Eastern Churches and founded what is considered the first hospital in history.\n\nGregory Nazianzen was his closest friend and fellow theologian. Together they shaped the Church's understanding of the Trinity and the Holy Spirit.\n\nBoth were declared Doctors of the Church and are revered in both East and West.`,
    quote: `A tree is known by its fruit; a man by his deeds. A good deed is never lost; he who sows courtesy reaps friendship, and he who plants kindness gathers love.`,
