    feast_date: '01-17',
    birth_year: '251',
    death_year: '356',
    biography: `Anthony was an Egyptian monk who became the father of desert monasticism. Born to wealthy parents, he gave away his possessions after hearing the Gospel call to sell all and follow Christ, and retreated to the desert for over eighty years.\n\nHe attracted disciples who formed the first monastic communities, and his life recorded by Athanasius of Alexandria inspired countless men and women to pursue the contemplative life.\n\nHe is said to have lived to the age of 105 and remained vigorous in mind and body to the end.`,
