    id: 's-0124',
    name: 'Saint Francis de Sales',
    feast_date: '01-24',
    birth_year: '1567',
    death_year: '1622',
    biography: `Francis de Sales was Bishop of Geneva during the Counter-Reformation. Rather than use force or condemnation against Calvinist heretics, he embarked on a gentle mission of preaching, writing, and personal example that won back many thousands of converts.\n\nHis writings, especially Introduction to the Devout Life and Treatise on the Love of God, showed that holiness was possible for people in every state of life, not only monks and priests.\n\nHe co-founded the Order of the Visitation with Saint Jane de Chantal and was declared Doctor of the Church in 1877, and patron of writers and journalists.`,
    quote: `Do not wish to be anything but what you are, and try to be that perfectly.`,
