    id: 's-0128',
    name: 'Saint Thomas Aquinas',
    feast_date: '01-28',
    birth_year: '1225',
    death_year: '1274',
    biography: `Thomas Aquinas was an Italian Dominican friar, philosopher, and theologian whose synthesis of Aristotelian philosophy and Christian theology — known as Thomism — remains one of the most influential systems of thought in Western history.\n\nHis Summa Theologica, left unfinished at his death, attempted a comprehensive account of Christian theology. Near the end of his life he reportedly said that all his writings seemed like straw compared to what he had experienced of God in prayer.\n\nHe was declared a Doctor of the Church in 1567 and is the patron of students and scholars.`,
    quote: `To one who has faith, no explanation is necessary. To one without faith, no explanation is possible.`,
