    id: 's-0131',
    name: 'Saint John Bosco',
    feast_date: '01-31',
    birth_year: '1815',
    death_year: '1888',
    biography: `John Bosco was an Italian priest who dedicated his life to the education and care of poor and at-risk youth in Turin. Born into poverty himself, he worked to give boys practical skills, education, and above all a knowledge of God.\n\nHis educational philosophy — the Preventive System — emphasized love, reason, and religion rather than punishment and fear. He founded the Salesian Society and the Daughters of Mary Help of Christians.\n\nHe is said to have experienced prophetic dreams from childhood. He was canonized in 1934.`,
